# 2026-06-22 23:01:56.108044
+Review the Category Detail Page implementation and complete the migration from the old mock contract to the new backend API contract.
+
+UX EXPECTATIONS (IMPORTANT)
+====================================================
+
+This is NOT a product listing page.
+
+This page is an editorial discovery layer.
+
+The user should:
+
+1. Understand the category.
+2. Explore subcategories.
+3. Decide where to go next.
+
+The page should feel:
+
+- Premium
+- Modern
+- Calm
+- Editorial
+- Image-first
+
+Avoid:
+
+- Dashboard layouts
+- Utility-heavy layouts
+- Filter-heavy layouts
+- Dense grids
+- Product-listing appearance
+
+Mobile UX requirements:
+
+- Hero image must remain visible above the fold.
+- Category title should appear immediately.
+- Avoid excessive vertical whitespace.
+- Avoid large empty screens.
+- Subcategories should be easy to scan and tap.
+- Cards should stack naturally on mobile.
+- Maintain generous spacing without creating empty gaps.
+
+Current issue:
+
+The page contains excessive vertical whitespace above the category content.
+
+The Hero should establish the category immediately and should not create a large empty area when image/content is missing.
+
+TARGET PAGE STRUCTURE
+====================================================
+
+Hero
+↓
+Editorial Introduction
+↓
+Explore Subcategories
+↓
+Refine Entry
+
+Products must NEVER appear.
+
+Filters must NEVER appear.
+
+NEW BACKEND API CONTRACT
+====================================================
+
+{
+  id,
+  name,
+  permalink,
+  description,
+
+  media: {
+    cover_image: {
+      url
+    }
+  },
+
+  editorial: {
+    introduction
+  },
+
+  explore: {
+    subcategories
+  },
+
+  refine
+}
+
+TASKS
+====================================================
+
+1. Fix CategoryHero
+
+The component still uses old mock fields:
+
+- category.image
+- category.title
+- category.shortDescription
+
+Replace with:
+
+- category.media?.cover_image?.url
+- category.name
+- category.description
+
+Requirements:
+
+- Handle missing image gracefully.
+- Avoid excessive empty space when image is missing.
+- Keep premium editorial styling.
+- Hero should immediately communicate the category.
+
+----------------------------------------------------
+
+2. Fix EditorialOverview
+
+Remove usage of old fields:
+
+- editorialText
+- shortDescription
+- title
+
+Use:
+
+category.editorial?.introduction
+
+Fallback:
+
+category.description
+
+----------------------------------------------------
+
+3. Review CategoryDetail Type
+
+Ensure all TypeScript types match the backend payload.
+
+Remove references to:
+
+- title
+- image
+- shortDescription
+- editorialText
+
+----------------------------------------------------
+
+4. Review ExploreSubcategories
+
+Use:
+
+category.explore.subcategories
+
+Each item should navigate to:
+
+/products?category=<subcategory.permalink>
+
+Keep current implementation if already correct.
+
+Do not convert this into a product grid.
+
+----------------------------------------------------
+
+5. Fix RefineEntry
+
+Use:
+
+/products?category=<category.permalink>&refine=1
+
+instead of:
+
+/products?category=<slug>&refine=1
+
+----------------------------------------------------
+
+6. Remove Dead Code
+
+Remove any remaining references to:
+
+- ExploreBrands
+- getBrandsByCategory
+- getThemesByCategory
+- mock category API fields
+- unused imports
+- unused types
+
+----------------------------------------------------
+
+7. Review Image Handling
+
+Ensure CategoryHero image uses the same image URL handling strategy as the Categories Listing Page.
+
+Use getImageUrl() if necessary.
+
+Image loading should behave consistently between:
+
+- Categories Listing Page
+- Category Detail Page
+
+----------------------------------------------------
+
+8. Architecture Constraints
+
+Do NOT:
+
+- Rename files
+- Move files
+- Introduce new sections
+- Redesign the page
+- Refactor unrelated code
+
+Keep the smallest possible diff.
+
+DELIVERABLE
+====================================================
+
+Before applying changes:
+
+1. Show all files that will be modified.
+2. Explain why each file needs changes.
+3. Highlight any API/type mismatches discovered.
+4. Then apply the changes.

