# 2026-06-23 18:26:03.354229
+Focus on React architecture, UX design patterns, component composition, Next.js App Router, and frontend engineering best practices. The goal is to build maintainable, production-quality React applications while learning scalable UI architecture.
+
+Task:
+Refactor the session stage components to use the existing React/Tailwind design system instead of the generated stage__* CSS classes.
+
+Files:
+
+* features/sessions/components/stage/PlayerStage.tsx
+* features/sessions/components/stage/GalleryStage.tsx
+* features/sessions/components/stage/InstagramStage.tsx
+* features/sessions/components/stage/GatewayStage.tsx
+
+Requirements:
+
+General:
+
+* Remove all stage__* and stage--* class names.
+* Use Tailwind utility classes only.
+* Follow existing project patterns and component architecture.
+* Use Next.js Image component instead of img.
+* Do not introduce CSS modules.
+* Do not introduce custom CSS files.
+* Preserve all media payload types defined in features/sessions/types.ts.
+* Keep Stage.tsx unchanged.
+
+PlayerStage:
+
+* Use aspect-video layout.
+* Use rounded-3xl container.
+* Show poster image before play.
+* Show large centered play button.
+* Replace poster with full-width iframe/video player after play.
+* Support:
+
+  * youtube_video
+  * youtube_live
+  * uploaded_video
+* Display live badge for youtube_live.
+
+GalleryStage:
+
+* Large featured image.
+* Thumbnail strip below.
+* Clicking a thumbnail changes the featured image.
+* Responsive layout.
+* Use existing design-system spacing conventions.
+
+InstagramStage:
+
+* Editorial card layout.
+* Large image/poster.
+* CTA: "View on Instagram".
+* Open in new tab.
+
+GatewayStage:
+
+* Editorial card layout.
+* Large image/poster.
+* CTA: "Open Experience".
+* Open in new tab.
+
+Architecture Goals:
+
+* Keep components small and composable.
+* Prefer clear React patterns over clever abstractions.
+* Use TypeScript discriminated unions correctly.
+* Optimize for readability and learning React architecture.
+* Match the visual language used elsewhere in the react-event project.
+
+Expected Outcome:
+
+* All 6 media types render correctly:
+
+  * youtube_video
+  * youtube_live
+  * uploaded_video
+  * image_gallery
+  * instagram_post
+  * external_link
+* Session Details page looks visually consistent with the rest of the application.
+* No references remain to stage__* or stage--* classes.
+

