+Project: react-event
+
+Review and improve the Product Listing Page using the current Crafted design system.
+
+Files to review:
+
+features/products/components/navigation/DesignerSpotlight.tsx
+features/products/components/navigation/CategoryNavigation.tsx
+features/products/components/layout/ProductsHeader.tsx
+features/products/components/grid/EmptyState.tsx
+
+Goals:
+
+1. Designer Spotlight
+
+* Current implementation feels like floating metadata.
+* Keep it editorial and luxury.
+* Keep a subtle heading (e.g. "Featured Designers").
+* Do NOT use pills, tags, bordered buttons, or chip UI.
+* Designers should feel curated, not filter controls.
+* Use typography, spacing, and hierarchy similar to SSENSE, Net-a-Porter, and MyTheresa.
+* Preserve existing filter behavior.
+
+2. Product Listing Page Titles
+
+* Remove CMS-looking titles such as:
+  "Themes/Modern Ceremony Collection"
+* Generate clean editorial titles:
+  "Modern Ceremony"
+  "Modern Ceremony Collection"
+  "Bridal"
+  "Saffron Loom"
+* Do not expose taxonomy paths or internal data structures.
+
+3. Category Navigation
+
+* Current navigation became too quiet after cleanup.
+* Reintroduce subtle context.
+* Add a restrained editorial label such as:
+  "Collections"
+* Avoid visual noise.
+* Keep products as the primary focus.
+* Do not bring back heavy blur effects, oversized indicators, or decorative chrome.
+
+4. Empty State
+   Replace generic ecommerce copy:
+
+"No products found"
+
+with a more editorial luxury tone.
+
+Examples:
+
+* "No pieces match the current selection."
+* "Try adjusting your selections or explore another collection."
+
+Keep it concise and elegant.
+
+Requirements
+
+* Do not redesign the page.
+* Do not change layout structure.
+* Do not introduce new components.
+* Do not add animations.
+* Do not add decorative luxury elements.
+* Stay consistent with the existing Crafted typography system.
+* Preserve accessibility.
+* Explain the planned changes first.
+* Then implement.

