+Goal
+
+Complete the Product Details Page (PDP) using data that already exists in the current API payload.
+
+Important Constraints
+
+* Do NOT redesign the hero/gallery layout.
+* Do NOT redesign typography.
+* Do NOT redesign spacing system.
+* Do NOT introduce new design patterns.
+* Do NOT modify PLP, Categories, Brands, Programs, Sessions, or shared design-system components.
+* Do NOT add backend changes.
+* Do NOT change API contracts.
+* Do NOT add mock recommendation products.
+* Do NOT add wishlist, reviews, ratings, checkout, cart, or ecommerce functionality.
+* Do NOT add a floating CTA bar.
+* Do NOT add a sticky CTA bar.
+* Keep all existing visual language and design tokens.
+
+Only implement the items below.
+
+---
+
+1. Fix existing PDP data binding issues
+
+---
+
+Verify and fix:
+
+* Brand name displays correctly from:
+  product.brand.name
+
+* Product price displays correctly from:
+  product.price
+
+Remove any incorrect references such as:
+
+* product.brand_name
+
+Use only the existing API payload.
+
+---
+
+2. Gallery single-image handling
+
+---
+
+Current payload frequently contains only one gallery image.
+
+If:
+
+gallery.length <= 1
+
+Then:
+
+* Hide thumbnail rail completely.
+* Show only the primary image.
+* Avoid rendering a thumbnail list with a single duplicate image.
+
+Do not redesign multi-image behavior.
+
+---
+
+3. Themes and Occasions
+
+---
+
+Using:
+
+themes[]
+occasions[]
+
+Render understated metadata near the product information area.
+
+Example:
+
+Royal Heritage
+Wedding Ceremony
+Reception
+
+Requirements:
+
+* Quiet editorial treatment.
+* Not pills/chips.
+* No heavy borders.
+* No colorful badges.
+* Hide section when arrays are empty.
+
+---
+
+4. Designer Note section
+
+---
+
+Create a new PDP section:
+
+Designer Note
+
+Source:
+
+designer_note
+
+Requirements:
+
+* Render only when data exists.
+* Section should return null when missing.
+* Editorial presentation.
+* No placeholder text.
+
+---
+
+5. Product Details section
+
+---
+
+Create a new PDP section:
+
+The Details
+
+Source:
+
+details:
+
+* material
+* craft
+* origin
+* care
+* fit
+* delivery
+
+Requirements:
+
+* Render only populated fields.
+* Hide empty values.
+* Two-column specification layout on desktop.
+* Simple stacked layout on mobile.
+* Return null if all fields are empty.
+
+---
+
+6. Craft Story section
+
+---
+
+Create a new PDP section:
+
+The Craft
+
+Source:
+
+craft_story.title
+craft_story.description
+
+Requirements:
+
+* Render only when data exists.
+* Return null when missing.
+* Text-focused presentation.
+* No mock imagery.
+
+---
+
+7. About the Maison section
+
+---
+
+Create a new PDP section:
+
+About [Brand Name]
+
+Source:
+
+product.brand.story
+product.brand.founded_year
+product.brand.origin
+
+Requirements:
+
+* Render only available values.
+* Return null if no content exists.
+* Text-focused layout.
+* Do NOT create hero banners.
+* Do NOT use cover images yet.
+* Do NOT create large marketing blocks.
+
+Example structure:
+
+About Saffron Loom
+
+Founded 2014
+Jaipur, India
+
+Brand story...
+
+---
+
+8. More From Brand section
+
+---
+
+Source:
+
+recommendations.more_from_brand
+
+Requirements:
+
+* Reuse existing ProductCard.
+* Reuse existing product grid patterns.
+* Do not create a new card design.
+* Hide section entirely when array is empty.
+* Do not create mock products.
+
+---
+
+9. Request Quote interaction
+
+---
+
+Keep existing Request Quote CTA.
+
+Implement a lightweight UI only.
+
+Requirements:
+
+* Clicking Request Quote opens a modal or slide-over.
+* Collect:
+
+  * Name
+  * Email
+  * Phone
+  * Message
+
+For now:
+
+* No backend submission.
+* No API calls.
+* No form persistence.
+
+Submit button may simply close the modal and show a success state.
+
+This is a UX stub only.
+
+---
+
+10. Graceful Empty Handling
+
+---
+
+All new sections must:
+
+* Return null when required data is missing.
+* Never render empty headings.
+* Never render placeholder lorem ipsum.
+* Never render fake content.
+
+---
+
+11. Deliverables
+
+---
+
+After implementation provide:
+
+1. Files created.
+2. Files modified.
+3. Component tree of the PDP.
+4. Any assumptions made.
+
+Do not make backend changes.
+Do not change API responses.
+Do not redesign the page.
+Focus only on assembling the luxury editorial experience from existing payload data.

